# Clean URL rewrites for DO Static Sites (Netlify-format).
#
# VitePress's `cleanUrls: true` generates internal links like `/embed/npm`
# while the actual file is `embed/npm.html`. Vue Router handles the mapping
# during SPA navigation, but a direct browser request goes straight to the
# host — DO doesn't strip `.html` on its own, so the page 404s.
#
# Rule format: `<from>  <to>  <status>`. With status 200 it's a rewrite
# (URL stays the same), not a redirect. Rewrites only fire when no static
# file matches the requested path, so this doesn't shadow /sdk/*, /og.png,
# etc.

/embed/*      /embed/:splat.html      200
/guide/*      /guide/:splat.html      200
/protocol/*   /protocol/:splat.html   200
/deploy/*     /deploy/:splat.html     200
